      "amount": "3 tablespoons"
    },
    {
      "name": "water chestnuts, sliced",
      "amount": "1 cup"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat sesame oil in a pan over medium heat.",
    "Add minced ginger and onion. Saut\u00e9 until onions become translucent.",
    "Stir in pistachio paste and red pepper flakes. Cook for about 2 minutes, stirring constantly to avoid burning.",
    "Pour in water chestnuts and soy sauce. Stir until the mixture thickens slightly.",
    "Reduce heat to low, add peanut butter and cumin seeds. Mix well.",
    "Add sliced capsicum and continue to cook for another 5-7 minutes or until all vegetables are tender but not mushy.",
    "Garnish with finely chopped coriander before serving."
  ],
